description:
The secret origin of the new Challengers of the Unknown! The Challengers' mysterious past is uncovered by Nina Justis, a huckster who specializes in the paranormal.

A muck-raking reporter investigates the team's lives and tries to stir up trouble for ratings.
name: Expose
Program Change Or My Mom, My Enemy!

description: California. The Flash's new base of superheroic operations. And major earthquake territory. Add Major Disaster to the mix and there's nothing but trouble for Santa Marta & Wally.
name: Cause and Effect

description: After last issue's unexpected finale, John must gather together his friends to formulate a plan against Myrddin. But as usual, things don't go according to plan. "Last Man Standing" part 4, the penultimate chapter of John Constantine's King Arthur-inspired epic.
name: Last Man Standing, Part 4 - You're Just A...

description: Impulse and his mom are in the 30th Century and their first goal is to free Iris Allen's parents from the captivity of the Science Police while staying one step ahead of being captured themselves!
name: You and Me against the World

description: Turbulent rain dances, transparent trains and psychic trances collide as King Mob discovers startling new info about the Roswell Event. Meanwhile, a revenge-driven Jolly Roger visits the genetic experimentation pens to learn the fate of her teammates and finally faces the nefarious Quimper.
name: Black Science, Part Four: Safe

description: The Marvel Family flies again…but it's not the Marvel Family anyone has ever seen before! Continuing the saga of the Fawcett City that was never-meant-to-be, Thaddeus Bodog Sivana's plan to realign the events that created Captain Marvel shifts into overdrive. In this issue, the new Captain Marvel is framed for murder, endangering his family's secret identities. Even the power of Shazam himself may not be able to prevent the next phase of Sivana's deadly scheme!
name: Hero Falls

description:
Find out the shocking story of how Cassidy became a vampire in "Cry Blood, Cry Erin," a 2-part story set during the Irish Republican Army's 1916 "Easter Rising."

The story of how a nice young Irish boy named Proinsias in 1916 became the hard-living, blood-sucking Cassidy.
name: Cry Blood, Cry Erin

description: Mitch Shelley awakens to fragments of a past life and strange, new abilities. He is the Resurrection Man and, once killed, rises again with a new power--some blessings, others curses that need to be stopped.
name: Resurrection Man

description: Robin reluctantly teams up with a smitten Spoiler to ambush the Ghost Dragons lair little knowing Lynx is in waiting.
name: Rebound

description:
Murder again hits a shady dime-novel press, but the gruesome methods are being foretold in their own books--and the police want to know why. Behind the scenes, the Golden Age Sandman delves deeper into an increasingly dangerous situation.

Includes a bonus classic Sandman tale with art by Daniel Torres
name: The Return of the Scarlet Ghost: Act Two of Four

story_arc_credits.name: The Return of the Scarlet Ghost

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Return of the Scarlet Ghost

description: Shade recounts his first several encounters with the Ludlow family's vendetta, including several that begin to question their rivalry.
name: Rupert and Marguerite: 1865 & 1931

description: "The Haunting of Jim Corrigan." Part 2: "Confrontation." Part 2 of 5. Attempting to free the death row inmate he saved, the Spectre tracks down some dirty cops. But even that might not help. Nate Kane, meanwhile, learns more about the Jim Corrigan mystery.
name: The Haunting of Jim Corrigan, Part Two: Confrontation

description:
Dr. Pip, an eccentric bomber, terrorizes Opal City. Unfortunately, with no demands, even the police can't figure out what motivates the sinister villain. Also, Jack hears from an old ally, for what could be the last time.

As The Infernal Dr. Pip makes his deadly mark on Opal City, one of the residents of the city believes that it is time to make the acquaintance of Jack Knight.
name: Infernal Devices, Part One

description: Kryptonian criminals Jax-Ur and Mala are encased in a miniature, sealed prison, but when a local disruption frees them, they make sure Superman gets to see things from their perspective--literally!
name: All Creatures Great and Small, Part 1

description: Wonder Womans body is reverting to the clay that she was first formed of by her mother, Hippolyta. But, returning to Themyscira, Diana finds that shes not the only Amazon so afflicted! Plus, Champion finally reveals his secret!
name: Stone May Grow

description: Jackie fights the Angelus during daylight and manages to escape from her. But not without taking a hostage with her. The Angelus is outraged and sends out all her warriors to find him, but Jackie is taking care of his own bussiness. However, Jenny learns the horrible truth behind Jackie.
name: Brought To Light

description: The Police, Freak Force, Underground Freaks, and the villainous Octopus attack Cyberface and the Vicious Circle at a downtown public rally they are holding, where they have crucified the captive Dragon.

Overview

After Cyan is returned safely to her parents, Al has a long talk with Granny Blake and as usual, her words of wisdom calm him while creating inner confusion. When he gets back to the alley, the alley bums have rebuilt his throne which seems to hypnotize him as he settles into it. The Clown appears in Spawn's trance and reveals startling facts about his past and future. Meanwhile, Wynn confrims Cy-Gor's remains are safe at a testing facility and orders the disappearance of Terry
name: Sanctuary

description:
Fury and de Fontaine are having a meeting with President Bill Clinton. He makes them tell the story of Captain America to them. Fury reveals some of what the President knows is true but some isn't. He reveals that the US Governement is responsible for Cap's disappearance after WWII. Cap was opposed to the atomic bomb and the governement saw this as a rebellion. SHIELD then put Cap into suspended animation.

Fury revealed that they thawed Cap when necessary to see if he was doing OK. They would reconfigure how he thought and put him into battle. In the Korean War he was known as Captain John Battle. In Vietnam he was Captain Jack Strike for Black Ops. But eventually, something would push Cap over the edge and SHIELD would put him back in suspended animation.

Cap was finally revived again in the 1990's and set up with a wife and family. SHIELD finally awoke the 'Captain America' in him when Red Skull was found to be alive.

As it turns out, Cap had been listening in on this conversation the whole time. Cap lets them know that he does not trust the government but he does love his country. He also lets Fury know that next time they try to suspend his life he will resist and that they do not want a war with him. Cap resigns his 'protection' from SHIELD and tells the president that he will still fight for his country. The president allows him to leave, tells Fury to let it go and do the right thing for once and wishes Cap the best of luck.
name: Crossroads

description: Insomnia pursues Karen, while supermodel Niomi flees from her stalker and arrives at Foggy's apartment. Meanwhile, Daredevil invades Kingpin's penthouse office at WFSK. And in the end, an old foe.
name: No Rest for the Wicked

description:
An army of assassins are turning NYC into a bloodbath, and there's only one way our anti-hero can survive! That's right, Elektra's back to her old wicked ways. Meanwhile, the ancient being known only as the Architect offers Konrad Weiss what he's always wanted - but to get it, Konrad will have to sell out Elektra.

Assassins are descending on Manhattan to compete to prove they are worthy to assassinate the Architect and claim the reward. Elektra aims to stop them, but her fighting ability only impresses him, and she earns the spot.
name: Out of the Night

description:
At the mercy of Bastion, could Jubiee really be the sole survivor of the X-Men?

Bastion tries to manipulate the captive Jubilee into revealing secrets of the X-Men. He shows her false evidence of the deaths of Cyclops and Bishop in order to evoke memories, but he learns nothing useful.

Back at Xavier's School for Gifted Children, Emma Frost probes Sean Cassidy's mind to search for clues of the possible whereabouts of the missing Gen X'ers. A memory of the original X-Men bound in vines sparks a realization in Sean and he hastily flies off.

At Bastion's base, an image of a tortured Wolverine begging for mercy merely makes Jubilee laugh, knowing it is false. A frustrated Bastion recalls his own memory then, and the images are transmitted to the monitors. His assistant, Daria, watches as onscreen, a mechanical hand is enveloped by a skin-like substance, then the hand is revealed to belong to Bastion. He takes his leave, ordering Daria to commence "Operation: Zero Tolerance".
name: The Last X-Man

description: Hulk faces off with another Hulk from an alternate future. In the other Hulk's future, Hulk had to kill the Maestro. The Hulk from the future wanted to warn our Hulk so he wouldn't make the same mistakes, but he gets pulled back to his timeline before he can.
name: Lock and Key

description: Ka-Zar is developing an unhealthy obsession with outside technology. But this is the least of his problems as evil men target his family, specifically his infant son.
name: The Thrilling Return of Ka-Zar, Lord of the Savage Land!

description: This is a behind the scenes of the very first pilot episode of the Cage.  It is from the perspective of J. Mia Colt.  Mia has the unfortunate task of replacing Dermot Cusack.  Dermot was Captain Christopher Pike's Yeoman and long time friend who died in a battle at Rigel VII.  She arrives on the U.S.S. Enterprise just as the coffins are being unloaded.  She is not wanted as Dermot was so popular and it takes time before she is respected by the crew.  At the end of the story is some of the early sketches of the crew.
name: Nor Iron Bars a Cage

description: LaForge and Abrams must sabotage and Romulan engine project. Plus a bonus story of Scotty doing similar years ago.
name: None But The Brave; Inheritance

description: Why must Captain Janeway forge an uneasy alliance with a band of her most dreaded enemies? Because the race is on for an ancient relic that gives its owner the power to rule the universe! If Janeway doesn't find it first, the U.S.S. Voyager, along with the entire Delta Quadrant, may be destroyed!
name: Relicquest, Part Two

description:
The team meet their first Torg robot and are faced with finding a way into Alia Rellapor's beautiful castle.  
 
Loza Throck returns and has a very interesting conversation with Poog.
Rain, Ben, and Traci road trip to San Francisco-- and while visiting the Sutro Bath house Rain enters a cave and discovers herself transported to the past!
name: The Road To You, Getting There: Part One

story_arc_credits.name: The Road To You, Getting There

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Road To You, Getting There

description:
Reprints the back-up stories that were originally in the Classic X-men issues #10, #17, #23 & #21:-

  1. Tag, Sucker!
  2. A Taste For Vengeance!
  3. High Adventure
  4. Just Love
name: Tag, Sucker!

description:
Jaeger meets Brigham to give him photos of his children, but Brig is unsatisfied with this and wants to know where they are. Meanwhile, Lynne uses the medical regulator connected to Marcie's headjack to insert a program into her subconscious as a contingency against their father returning.

Jaeger interrogates Brigham about why he thinks his family fled from him three years ago. Brigham gets flustered and tries to avoid the question, blaming Emma for being a flake.

Elsewhere, Emma is at a jobsite in one of her trance states. Blythe informs her of an incoming call but is told to take a message. Emma collapses again, singing old song lyrics while unconscious. Information is an irresistible currency to an artificial intelligence, and Blythe begins recording the lyrics once she is able to rationalize eavesdropping to herself.

Brigham asserts to Jaeger that Rachel takes more after her father's clan, starkly contrasted by a flashback showing how the Medawars looked down on Rachel for being a half-blood. As Jaeger and Brigham's argument continues, it's revealed that Lynne has been eavesdropping on their conversation via the bug he planted on Jaeger's boot in Finder #2. (In fact, we see Lynne listening in just as Jaeger refers to him as "devious, and I don't mean little-kid devious, either.")

Jaeger is still unsure whether Brigham is a danger to his family or not and decides he must test him. He gives Brigham a card with Emma's address (in later issues it's shown that the address is a fake Jaeger deliberately set up so he could observe Brigham's behavior.)
name: Finder
Replacement God
Guys Part 18

description:
Aquaman's powers are out of control, and Swamp Thing helps Aquaman defeat a two-bit villain in order to prove this to him, and give him the help he needs.

Aquaman swims across a rotting corpse in a bed of seaweed, and is taken aback when the seaweed coalesces into the Swamp Thing. Aquaman rashly lashes out with his telepathy, quickly finding himself entangled in the seaweed bed the Swamp Thing is manipulating. The briefest of conversations convinces the two antagonists that neither is the monster they believed the other to be. Due to a rotting corpse washing up on the shore of Star Bay, the mayor shuts down the popular tourist attraction. When questioned by his staff, the mayor produces a ransom note, requesting three million dollars, signed by someone calling themselves "Toxin". A bit of rotting undersea vegetation accompanied the note, the same flora found throughout the dead man's body. As the mayor relays this information, a member of his staff begins choking on the salad he was consuming. Suddenly, plant life bursts from the man's gullet, killing him. The mayor resolves to pay the ransom. Swamp Thing's connection to the Green provides him with awareness of the plant related murder. It also leads him to suspect that one of the men in the mayor's office was actually responsible for that death. Aquaman and Swamp Thing stake out the mayor's office, waiting for someone to leave to deliver the ransom money. As the mayor drives away, Aquaman slices off Swamp Thing's left hand, with his harpoon, then fires the appendage at the car. While waiting for the car to reach it's destination, Swamp Thing comments on Aquaman's current situation, comparing the Sea King to an alcoholic vagrant sleeping in the alley behind them. Both men have lost control of their lives. Swamp Thing offers to help Aquaman with his dilemma, but the Sea KIng refuses.

The Mayor hurls the briefcase holding the ransom money into the sea. It is picked up by Patti Matson, the lifeguard who found the dead man's body. Aquaman closes on Matson, who retaliates by firing an array of harpoons at the Sea KIng, from her high tech sea sled. Aquaman easily dodges the barrage, but is surprised to find that the harpoons are tracking him. Aquaman lassos the missiles with his own harpoon line, just as Matson releases mines into the water. Swamp Thing grows a new body from his severed hand, still clinging to the mayor's car, and confronts the mayor. Upon seeing the Swamp Thing, the mayor attacks, using his own power to control flora against the plant elemental. Aquaman telepathically orders a school of fish to provide him with a momentary distraction. The fish, however, terrified of Aquaman, due to the mutagenic changes that have, of late, befallen him, refuse to assist him. Matson fires on Aquaman with laser cannons, enraging the Sea KIng enough to throw caution to the wind, and engage her head on. Aquaman grabs Matson's sea sled and hurls it out of the sea, crashing it into the mayor's car. Aquaman loops his harpoon line around the mayor's leg, and throws him out to sea. Matson spears Aquaman in the back, further enraging the already volatile Sea King. Swamp Thing entangles the mayor in sea greens, then carries him back to shore. At this point, Aquaman has gained the advantage over Matson. Out of control, the Sea KIng is broadcasting telepathic commands into Matson's brain, causing her to repeat everything Aquaman is yelling at her. Swamp Thing enters Aquaman's mind, to expose the root rot in the Sea King's soul that has poisoned his telepathic abilities. With the full realization of what has happened to him revealed, Aquaman begs the Swamp Thing to help him.
name: Sea of Green

description:
The JLA encounter an enemy from the future!

The issue starts off with the burial of Metamorpho and JLA starting a recruitment drive. They add a new member of the team that comes in the form of Tomorrow Woman. What the JLA don't know is that Tomorrow Woman is an android and was built by Professor Ivo and T.O. Morrow to infiltrate and destroy the league. While the team battles the "If" they are assisted by Tomorrow Woman who ends up overcoming her programing and not only does not hurt anyone in the league but she also sacrifices her life to stop the "If". Ironically Superman is the only one seen at her burial.

Special Note:

During the burial of Metamorpho there are multiple statures of fallen Justice League members. The Statues are of Green Arrow (Oliver Queen), Green Lantern (Hal Jordan), Ice, Metamorpho, Doctor Mid-Nite (Charles McNider), Flash (Barry Allen) and Jesse Quick.
name: Woman of Tomorrow

description: Dr. Killebrew mentions to Deadpool that the healing process is going fine, and that he will recover with just a little more time. Deadpool is glad to hear that, but instead of thanking the doctor, he moves over to his plan to… kill Killebrew! Meanwhile, down at the Hellhouse, when Weasel mentions Deadpool’s name, T-Ray gets upset. Since he dislikes Deadpool, not to say hate, he is planning an attack on the merc-with-a-mouth, and tells anyone with a brain to move over to his side and not to put up with Wade anymore. When Patch enters, T-Ray stops his speech. Patch has a new assignment, which involves killing some people, and T-Ray accepts it. After an argument with her, Siryn manages to calm Deadpool down, and just to accept Killebrew’s gift. She promises that whatever personal issues Wade has, he doesn’t have to face them alone anymore and can always count on her help whenever needed. Deadpool and Siryn leave, but Deadpool warns Killebrew to look up his other victims, and help them the way he helped him. Siryn and Wade return to the Xavier Institute, where they go to sit on the roof. Wade talks about his feelings for Siryn but, since she is too busy with being leader of X-Force, she doesn’t have the proper time for a relationship. But, she promises Wade that, when she gets her head back together and if Wade stays on the path she thinks he is on right now, it might happen in the future. That’s good enough for Wade, and they move closer together, and watch the snow falling down. At the same time, T-Ray finishes his job. He goes to sit in a circle he made, where he honors his victims deaths. He takes a look at his back, which has a big “X” insignia on it, marked through the names of his victims. Deadpool is there as well, but the name is untouched so far. T-Ray promises himself that it will stay that way for at least a little while, but not forever.
name: The Doctor Is Skinned! or The End Of Our First Story Arc

description: A Stormwatch crew deal with an old Daemonite site.

PKNA #5

Ritratto dell'eroe da giovane / Portrait of the Young Hero
name: Ritratto dell'eroe da giovane

description: Nightwing got a few hits in on Blockbuster, but he was eventually defeated. Soames convinced Desmond that killing him would only bring Batman (not a good idea). Nightwing woke up in the middle of a biker gang. He escaped; Blockbuster took them out single-handedly due to their inability to kill him.
name: The Bigger They Are

description:
It's 1958 and the Legionnaires are students in Mr. Swan's Art Class at Happy Harbor High School, frantically preparing for a visit from the President of the United States. Unexpectedly, this idyllic scenario comes crashing down around them when Happy Harbor is invaded by a monster from another planet.

Gates finds himself in 1958, with his teammates amnesiacs believing themselves to be Curt Swan's high school art class students.
name: Swan's Way

description:
Overview

Couder is dead, his skull and spine ripped out, and Matteson is missing. That leaves the team no choice -- they have to go back into the waters to search for their absent comrade. They're prepared to battle a Predator, so they believe they're prepared for the worst, but the horrible truth is that the Predator may be the least of their troubles.

Stormwatch Prime is prepared by Henry Bendix, the Weatherman, to handle a powerful threat called The High. While the preparation occurs, Jenny Sparks is attacked by one of The High's teammates from the Changers, Blind. Blind is able to inject Jenny Sparks with several needles to incapacitate her, but she is able to release them and free herself. Meanwhile, Malcolm King, the former Stormwatch member known as Strafe that has gone mad, is granted an audience with the members of the Changers and is willing to give them all the information he knows about Stormwatch, the only group that could prove to be an obstacle to the Changers. They force Malcolm King to go through a rigorous interrogation with Blind while the rest of the Changers continue their plan about changing the world their own way. Meanwhile, Henry Bendix and Rose Tattoo, a former Changer, realize they have to kill the Changers to stop their plans.
name: Change Or Die: Part One Of Three

description: Includes the bonus story Cruise to Nightmare by Paul Dini and Bruce Timm.
name: You Can't Cheetah an Honest Man

description: Dirty Tricks part 1 of 3: A murderous villain from Bruce's past known as The Magician has appeared in Gotham, and is leaving a fresh trail of corpses in his wake.
name: Dirty Tricks: Part 1 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

name: Book Three
The Rookie

description: The true origin of Ninjak revealed! Denny Meechum travels to an ancient Japanese temple - in Maine of all places! There he finds the man who designed the Ninjak game. However, before he can get the answers he seeks, Denny will have to survive another attack by the Dark Dozen!
Zero takes the fight back to New Orleans to get rid of Tommy Lee Bones and his gang of Dead Men. Finally in control of the power of Shadowman, it's time to find out what that really means.
name: Deadside Part Four

description: Donovan's time as X-O Manowar has forced him to ignore his duties at his own company, Brainstorm Technologies. But when a disgruntled employee finds himself clumsily empowered by prototype tech, it will take more than human resources to shut him down.
name: Idea Man

description:
Overview

In the eighth great issue of BWS's visionary monthly extravaganza, Tristan Caine, The Paradoxman, has made an astonishing breakthrough in his perception of his whereabouts in the shifting tableau of time and reality that his life has become. In The Freebooters, Axus and his cohorts finish up their raid on the Kalif's palace while their less-than-charming host tries to convey to them that there are much graver perils to face than they had bargained for. And in Young Gods, Heros and Strangehands confront Destiny himself, while Aragon, Keeper of the Dragons, tries to rekindle his old acquaintance with the beguiling Princess Adastra.
OverviewIn the sewers of Paris and out of his element, Tarzan, Lord of the Jungle, faces the "civilized" monster of the concrete jungle: The Phantom of the Opera!
name: Le Monstre (Part 2 of 2)

description: The Man of Steel meets the Man of Madness as two of comics' most unique and revolutionary heroes cross-over (and how!). In each of their respective universes, Superman and Madman are involved in scientific experiments, the results of which propel the unsuspecting superbeings into one another's world. The only thing is, each takes half of the other with him -- creating two confused heroes and one big Hullabaloo! It's wackier than red kryptonite and more bizarre than Bizarro when two worlds get an even stranger visitor from another planet -- Supermadman! And it doesn't stop there, because unexplainable things begin happening all around them. So the unexplainable has to be explained and the impossible made possible.
name: Man and Super-Madman

description:
Overview
His final spell worked. Elric vanquished the Lords of Chaos. But now he is weak, and at the mercy of Jagreen Lern. Hoisted atop the villain's sailing vessel, Elric is being kept just this side of death. Why go to all the trouble? "Because I want you to witness for yourself the defeat of the South," Lern gloats. "I want you to know that what you sought to avert will come to pass." So continues P. Craig Russell's adaptation of Elric: Stormbringer, the grand story of the final battle between Law and Chaos. Co-published with Topps Comics.
name: Chaos Warps

description:
Overview

Batman uses all his formidable detective skills to discover the identity of the serial killer Faceless and the identity of the fiend's next victim. But is he too late?

Batman and Robin delve deeper into the case to try to find the patterns behind the murders of a strange killer who takes the faces of his victims off.

Batman suddenly realises a frightening pattern that may pose Vesper at risk of her life.
name: Faceless, Part 2: Postmarked Murder

description: Young Olympic champion Helena Bertinelli witnesses her family brutally murdered and vows to bring down those responsible. Is Gotham's underworld ready for the Huntress? And more importantly, is Batman?
name: Duty of the Huntress

description:
When Two-Face tries to steal a rare edition of Stevenson's Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde, he learns that a woman dressed like a cat has beaten him to it.

Two Face escapes Arkham Asylum yet again and plans to steal a Jekyll and Hyde book worth 2 million. Catwoman and She Cat get involved when She-Cat had already robbed the book and tries to sell it to Zee, an already known associate of Catwoman's.
name: Two Cats in One

description: The Challengers are called to a grisly family murder...committed by a child! Plus, Clay Brody goes on a sudden and mysterious rampage!
name: Private Lives

description: It's the final confrontation between Flash and Major Disaster. Will Santa Marta be left standing after it's all over? Plus, who are the mysterious villains lurking in the background, poised to create a hell on Earth for Wally?
name: Trial Run

description: In "Last Man Standing" part 5, John Constantine's master plan comes together! It's the modern magician versus the ultimate magician of myth as the latest HELLBLAZER epic concludes!
name: Last Man Standing, Part 5 - No One Is Innocent

description: When Bart makes his triumphant return home to Manchester, he finds Max and everything else in the house gone. This leaves the impulsive youth to fend for himself--and that can't be a good thing!
name: Scorched

description: In part 1 of a 3-part storyline, The Invisibles hit the streets of San Francisco where they discover a nasty apocalyptic cult, a Japanese inventor's mysterious time machine and King Mob's tragic torch. As the team takes the scenic route stateside, more of Ragged Robin's precarious past is revealed.
name: Time Machine Go

description: This issue also contains the last appearence of the M. F. Enterprises version of Captain Marvel from 1967 that who had the power to split into parts and have those parts fly around.
name: The Tenants of Time

description:
In the conclusion of a special 2-part story chronicling Cassidy's early adventures in the United States, the vampiric buddy of Jesse Custer bumps shoulders with hard-drinking writers and free-loving hippies.

Cassidy continues to tell his story of how he spent the 20th century; pledges his absolute gratitude and trust to Jesse.
name: To the streets of Manhattan I wandered away

description: As the JLA battles the giant cyborg Amazo, Resurrection Man keeps low to the ground trying to pick up the pieces and save the un-powered suddenly caught in a storm of super-humans at war. He dies for the common man and is reborn with a power to rival both the JLA and Amazo.
name: Bystanders

description:
Crocky the Corcodile is on the loose; robbing stores at gunpoint and ruining the family friendly image of Crocky to young impressionable children who normally idolise him.

Only Robin is available to bring down the culprit.
name: Crock Around the Clock

description: A mysterious crime wave in the seedy pulp publishing business has turned horrendously personal for Wesley Dodds. As the love of his life, Dian Belmont, lies in a coma following the bombing of a shady publisher's office, the Golden Age Sandman verges on brutality as he hunts the culprits!
name: The Return of the Scarlet Ghost : Act Three of Four

story_arc_credits.name: The Return of the Scarlet Ghost

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Return of the Scarlet Ghost

description: Shade tries on the mantle of "super villain," tangling with Jay Garrick, who he views as a worthy opponent. He also uncovers the villainy of a dark new hero.
name: The Spider: 1951

description: Michael Holt has nothing to live for…until he meets the Spectre. Relating the tale of how the Justice Society tracked down the killer of the original Mr. Terrific, the Spectre convinces Holt to take on the role. This issue ties up threads left over from Justice League of America (1960-) numbers 171 and 172.
name: The Haunting of Jim Corrigan, Part Three: Atonement

description:
Dr. Pip finds Starman is too much for him to handle, so he brings in some metahuman help--a villain ready to put the bite on Jack Knight. Plus, more on the history of the Black Pirate.

As Jon Valor, The Black Pirate shares the tragic tale of his end with Jack, a mysterious figure hunts transistor radios among the antique shops around the Opal before meeting with The Infernal Mr. Pip!
name: Infernal Devices, Part Two

description: A miniaturized Superman comes face-to-face, more-or-less, against a giant-sized Jax-Ur! Unable to grow back to normal size, Metropolis stands helpless against the rampaging Kryptonian!
name: All Creatures Great and Small, Part 2

description: The Gods of Olympus are back! Are they the power behind the malady that's causing Wonder Woman and her sister Amazons to turn to clay?
name: Judgment Of The Gods

description: Jane's first big adventure starts in the streets of New York as she is forced into saving her enemy's daughter from a kidnapping.
name: The Big Wet Kiss Off

person_credits.name: Roberta Gregory
person_credits.role: writer, editor, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Uncle Frankie tells Jackie about his father. Jackie makes a teal with The Angelus.
name: Apocalypse Shortly

description: As Chris Robinson announces his retirement from being Star, Horde assumes control of the Vicious Circle, much to the distress of Powerhouse, who quits the team. Dragon, who has discovered he is multi-lingual, returns home with a date, where he is attacked by Dung and Chaos & Control.

Overview

Spawn confronts Jason Wynn only to have his vengeful anger stymied once again. Wynn informs him that if he dies, Terry, Wanda & Cyan will be eliminated. Knowing that he doesn't bluff, Spawn turns it into a catch-22 situation. Later in the alley, chaos erupts when Spawn and Angela are thrown together to discuss the unraveling of the universe. An unknown force then heals Al's face. Meanwhile, Terry is informed about a neighborhood petition to force them out of the area.
name: Return
Serpents and Eagles: Part 1: A First Small Hisssss

description: Molten Man’s in a boardroom preparing to take part in the family business. But Mr. Fear crashes the meeting unleashing a strange gas! Matt Murdock dons his Daredevil duds and tries to get Osborn Industries back in business.
name: A Question of Trust

description:
If dreams could come true…

This issue contains two stories.

"Oh, Now I Get It..." - The missing Generation X kids, Husk, Chamber, Synch, M and Skin, find themselves in a relatively pleasant situation: Chamber's body is again whole; Synch and Jubilee run a ship-board day care; M's brother Darius is human. Skin, however, doesn't buy into it.

Meanwhile, in Bastion's New Mexico complex, a sympathetic Daria begs Jubilee to eat.

Back aboard the ship, Glorian reveals himself to Skin as the creator of the fantasy the Gen X'ers are living. Skin denies there's anything he desires, and the angry Glorian ends the illusion, while giving Skin one thing he did want: the quintet are sent to the L.A. barrio that is Skin's home.

"Ye Double Feature" - Aboard a Frost Industries jet over the Pacific Ocean, Banshee reveals to Emma Frost his memories of Krakoa the Living Island. As they comfort each other, worried about the fates of the missing students, they reach the coordinates where Krakoa once was, finding only the empty ship raised from the depths by Glorian.

Meanwhile, at Bastion's base, Jubilee breaks free of her restraints and stuns Daria. Triggered by the attack, Daria's body releases a swarm of nanotech 'bugs' programmed to seek out mutants.
name: Oh, Now I Get It...
